Ask HN: App Store 100K+ downloads how?
text:
App Store 100K+ how?

Hello, HN! I wrote a good application (I made it for myself, as I could not find a ready-made application with the necessary functionality), uploaded it to Google Play, users like the application madly, excellent ratings and reviews, of course Google reacts adequately, gives the first users and slowly gaining 100K+ downloads, then 200K+....

After a while, I make an application for Apple at the request of users, upload it to the App Store, almost no downloads. I started to feel a little sorry for the time spent, I wondered how to promote it for free? )

Ask HN: Name of the comic where a pelican and his friends fall into a computer
text:
Hey HN, I am trying to find the first "computer book" I read :)

It was a comic in which a pelican and his friends visit a data center.

The way I remember it, the story was that they figure out that by saying the magic word "abracadabra", you can get into a computer. And inside the computer, there are little devils doing all the computations by carrying around handkerchiefs. The handkerchiefs with a knot are the ones and the handkerchiefs without a knot are the zeros.

I remember how I learned binary encoding from this comic book when I was 12 or so. I read it in German at that time. Would be fun to read it again. But so far, I was not able to find it again.

Show HN: GPTKitten – access ChatGPT from Kitty terminal
text:
I was typing away in SQLite when I needed some help, and thought why I don't have ChatGPT in my terminal, so I made this. It automatically adds text from your terminal - e.g. user selection, last or current command output or screen content - and can be used either as autocomplete (kitten) or interactive chat (new window in the terminal).

Code is quite horrendous, I made it in about five different ways before coming to this and can't be bothered to make it cleaner right now, but I'll keep improving it in the coming days.
